com.fasterxml.clustermate.api

Class KeyRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fasterxml.clustermate.api.KeyRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<KeyRange>

    public class KeyRange
extends Object
implements Comparable<KeyRange>
    Logical slice of a KeySpace; a consecutive range of individual key values within value space, defined by two parameters: starting key value (inclusive), and length between 0 and length of KeySpace.

    Instances have natural ordering based on getStart(), ascending.

      • clockwiseDistance

        public int clockwiseDistance(KeyHash key)
        Method that calculates clock-wise distance given key has, from beginning of this range. This is typically used to find the "closest" range for given key.
        NOTE: method does NOT check whether this range actually contains key (i.e. that contains(com.fasterxml.clustermate.api.KeyHash) would return true); it merely calculates distance from the start assuming range was large enough. If you want to verify containment, you may want to instead call clockwiseDistanceIfContained(KeyHash, int).
